Description:

Internship to grow and learn in the construction industry

Assist and support General contractor, Project Managers and Superintendents on assigned projects. The Project Management Intern must be a flexible and adaptable team-player, as well as have strong communication and organizational skills. Responsibilities may include, but are not limited to processing submittals and gathering and distributing information. The individual will work alongside the project team to manage high quality project documentation and process within budget and on schedule. This positions is also expected to attend project meetings and record meeting minutes, assist with the tracking and inspection of material deliveries and other miscellaneous tasks as assigned by the project team.

Required Skills:

*Spanish and English Bilingual 

• Excellent written and oral communication skills;

• Strong initiative and problem solving abilities;

• Outstanding attention to detail;

• Time management skills, with the ability to handle various responsibilities while meeting strict deadlines; Required Experience

• Pursuing a Bachelor’s Degree in Construction Management, Engineering, or relevant field required;

• Demonstrated interest in construction management and the construction industry


